caption: Great Thai restaurant! They have the best Thai dishes I have tried in Chicago. Staff is very kind and would definitely go again.
There are lots of good Thai spots in Chicago, but this place is my favorite. Be sure to order the crispy crepe!
Authentic Thai couple owners. Husband's name is Pramote. Great soups, salads & pork entrees.  🥰 Love Tom Kha soup & pad thai !
Exceptional Thai food. I'm convinced their peanut sauce is the best I've ever had. And they're really nice, too.
So good!
Authentic and delicious!

This is my all-time favorite Thai spot in Chicago. The fried chicken app is phenomenal. Wish they still had Yum-woon-sen salad, but they have so many alternatives it is very hard to be disappointed. Very Mom and Pop, BYOB,  small, easy to get a table, big dishes, great price, and super clean. Soft shell crab is great, all the curries are good, the salads are bomb, whatever fish sauce they put on the fried chicken is fugggn great. It can be a bit quiet in there, so bring some drinks to make sure you can keep the convo going with your guests, whenever the hell we can eat in again.
Great cooking, great people, delicious food. Please support Rainbow Thai.

Placed my very first order at 6:12pm for delivery, it is now 8:02pm still waiting.  Called in at 7:45pm and asked what was the hold up, the gentlemen kept asking me if I was Jimmy. I clearly stated no multiple times until I told him he should be asking me for my name first so we can track my order correctly.... once that was done they stated it was almost ready...... mind you I ordered 1 curry fired rice and 2 slices of cheesecake. How long should that take?  Gentleman did not apologize once, he did explain they could cancel my order or wait. I know they are not busy with dine-in due to stay at home order. Needless to say this will be my first and last order.
Waited over 90 minutes in store for an online order. That was after giving it the 25 minutes they told me it would take. Don't waste your time. Look elsewhere.

We love hanging out. Last night we went to this excellent place which friends told us about. We passed a delightful experience there with delicious meal and a well-trained crew and a distinguished  cuisine. We  added this fine restaurant in our phone list  and we shall no doubt return very soon. We highly recommend.

I arrive at this special place often  as I enjoy the good mood that is outline this restaurant. The personel is extremely helpful and skilfull. The service is impressively rapid. Needless to say, the food they serve is great. I have been there more than once and I was always happy. The rate is reasobable. I highly suggest this restaurant to to all.
I tried this place in the past with a friend and I am obsessed since then. I enjoy the great atmosphere and delicious food and drinks. I recommend this place.
Very well organised and welcoming spot. They provide generous portions and for affordable rates. I enjoyed the meals a lot and the staff were very personal and explanatory. Recommended.
Best Thai restaurant I’ve ever been. Our favorite restaurant. We eat here once a week.
The food and service were beyond our expectations. We absolutely enjoyed the atmosphere of this restaurant. Nice place to take my family out for lunch.

We really liked this place. We had the shrimp pad Thai and sticky rice. They got the order right and the delivery was fast. The only reason we took off one star is because it’s a little pricey for the amount you get. But a really good experience nonetheless
Great food, super friendly staff members, consistently good vibes. They charge convenient rates and the food quality is fantastic. Keep it up.
My favorite thai restaurant! Authentic. Decent priced.
This place sure knows how to treat their customers. Constantly with a very welcoming attitude. The food is conveniently priced, regularly fresh and clean.
Love their authentic that dishes. They are the real deal.
This place is to die for, excellent. The food presentation and ambiance was very nice.
Food is always delicious

Have been going to Rainbow Thai since it was a hole in the wall take out joint with 2 tables to eat in. The quality and the taste of the food has stayed the same. My favs are Thai fried chicken, crispy rice salad and the crispy pork.
Great BYOB Thai place with quick service and good food
Good Thai food.

The food here is pretty damn good, especially the Thai chicken appetizer. The issue is that they don't give you enough sauce for this dish. I asked for extra sauce of course (knowing that this is a problem) and received what's in the image below. It's like somebody is messing with me....it's a joke right? How is this enough sauce for 6 pieces of chicken??? You couldn't even fill one tiny plastic cup??? Get it together, c'mon!
We love this place. I'm thai and I alway come here
A fav place for quality Thai food. Definitely one of the best places in the area. I think I might become a regular. It has a nice feel to it. This place has good reviews for a reason.

Always have a great meal here.  Best Prik Khing curry in Chicago (on Sole Fish).  Always present owners who care about making your experience great.  Heat levels adjusted on request.  Love the BYOB option.  Don't miss the Gai Tod and Tod Mun.
Luv this place!! I come here too often but I always get taken care of well. Anna is a good waitress:)

This is our go-to place for authentic Thai food.  My wife and I have tried a lot of Thai restaurants and this one, by far, is the best in Chicago.  Some of our favorite from the menu are fried chicken, crispy rice salad, basic chicken, and Sole Fish (Pad Ped Pla).
The best.
One of my favorite thai restaurants here in the city. This place has great crab ragoons and great pad thai! The owner here, is so nice and is always a delight to see!
La Seafood glueless help no need to go there are so many better options around here
Don't remember

The food was inauthentic, with most dishes sweeter than what is normally the case--even in Chicago. The black pepper garlic chicken was particularly disappointing, as it was dry, cold, and completely flavorless. Service was attentive and polite. Decor was standard.
Great catfish

Amazing Thai food,original Thai food hard to find out,they're doing all of Thai salad,Thai curry,papaya salad,pretty well and very testy,here is real Five stars Thai food,thank you again,will come back soon.
Awesome Staff, Thai food is great. Ask, if you like spicy food, for extra flames.
Great flavor & priced accordingly
Loved the service, they are very friendly! Although, the foods expensive for the amount you get.

Love this little hole-in-the-wall place. It's funny they uploaded LTH's translation of their Thai menu (misspellings and all) to their regular menu so now anyone could order. My favorite: monk fish soup. Really need to take a pic of that soup and upload it. Sour and warm, great for cold day or sore throat when season changes.
Best Thai in Lincoln Square by far! Check out this hidden gem soon!
Will surely visit again.
The service isn't so bad the food is really good and the food is served pretty fast.
stopped by for take out and they were very friendly and quick and the curry was amazing! there's a $12 credit card minimum.
The food is delicious! Its a nice place to get a quick bite to eat!
Consistently the best carryout Thai in Chicago. This place is so good, get the crispy rice salad, trust me.
Wait is longer then expected

Absolutely amazing Thai cuisine. The space is not terribly warm or comfortable and the service can be spotty, but that's not why you go to this place. You go for the Issan sausage and the crispy rice salad and plenty of other terrific dishes that will transport you to another land.
Food is really bad. Worst service ever.
One of the best Thai restaurants, and my favorite. Their Pad Prik King with Shrimp is amazing. I would put that curry sauce on everything I eat if I could. Worth a trip.
Food poisoning
Most consistently excellent Thai food in Chicago - chef's quality control is amazing, even when they're packed.
Very good food and you can also make it spicy if you want. They have good spicy sauce. Nice and friendly spot environment
Quiet and peaceful. Good food and a very polite and attentive waiter.  Definitely a place I'd come back to.

Does Western Ave really need another Thai restaurant? If it's as good as Rainbow...yes! Clean bright flavors and spices. Friendly attentive staff. Nice seating area. Easy parking. I'll be back....soon!
Out of the world Naem Kao Tod... I get it every time!

Thai Rainbow is the best Thai food I've had anywhere. I love the food. I love the menu. They've made room for more dining in. The wait staff is incredibly friendly. They also do takeout and delivery witches really fast and convenient.

Been here a couple of times. The crispy fried rice and spicy basil dishes are excellent. The service...not so much. Both times I've been, it wasn't busy and yet the staff were nowhere to be found. It takes way too long to get refills or a drink, period. And then the food takes a long time also. My advice is to get take-out only from here.
Great food, quick delivery and nice staff.
The service was super friendly, the food so-so.
Great food, nice atmosphere, good prices.
Everything off the authentic Thai menu is fantastic. In a neighborhood with an abundance of top tier Thai options, this is a stand out.
Best authentic Thai in town. Famous for their naem keo Tod

Do not order delivery. It will never come and staff is incredibly rude. If you do not want people to order from grub hub or other delivery services, do not sign up. I wish that were the case, then I never would have heard of Rainbow and would not have waited 2 hours for food that's 10 minutes away and told that my food had been "out for delivery" for 45 min. Why would I still want it at that point?  Terrible food and customer service. Hard pass.
What a nice find!!! No frill type of place but the food is outstanding.  The deep fried chicken is so tasty. Pad Thai is delicious. Highly recommend this gem!!

Ordered from here twice now and both times took about 2 hours, which might be acceptable if we lived 90 minutes away.  However, since we live 8 minutes away and are ordering noodles, this is ridiculous.  Gave it a second chance thinking it was a fluke, but no good deed goes unpunished.  Will NEVER order from here again.

Very good Thai food! Love this place, it is definitely my go to Thai place.  In an area with this many Thai restaurants it is hard to choose one but this is my favorite.  Itty bitty but still they pack a punch with awesome food.  The red curry with duck is a personal favorite and the crab ragoon is a must try.
They are the nicest people.The wife is the cook and she is great.Love the rice salad. Never had anything like it in any thai restaurant. Don't expect fancy seating for only a dozen.

I love this hole-in-the-wall! Don't come and expect too much in terms of decor or service, but do expect a lot in terms of flavors, especially if you love spicy food like I do! The word on the street is that this place is the bona fide thai cuisine, but I just know it's REALLY good. Go visit this mom and pop place (the chef was also our server) , but bring your patience and appetite.
